Today is my first day back on my ADHD meds in basically 4 years, and I'm already noticing a positive difference.

Now though, I've made the decision to purposely wean my now 18 month old because it's time to put my own mental health first. It took a lot of time and thought and many discussions on the matter with my husband who has been so ridiculously supportive during this whole thing.
Even with all of that, I ultimately decided to breastfeed because of the benefits to both my babies and myself. I don't regret that decision, and if I have any more children, I will do so again.

I had to completely stop taking my ADHD meds, and my body didn't handle the transition from one depression medicine to a more pregnancy safe one, so I didn't take any until my second trimester because I was terrified of having a miscarriage. It was rough.

I almost didn't choose to breastfeed back when I was pregnant with Arya. Between having severe anxiety and depression and being ADD, it took me a long time finally find the right balance of medication to help my mental illnesses. My pregnancy put a halt to that.
This was not a decision taken lightly, especially since both Iris and I would probably be content going until even after she's turned 2.
It has officially been a week and a half since I stopped breastfeeding. After 4 years (minus a month) of straight being pregnant, breastfeeding, or both, this is an odd feeling.
